After the Xi-Biden meeting, the briefings of 🇨🇳 and 🇺🇸 used expressions such as the two presidents “agreed” “welcomed” “emphasized” for many times. This shows that although the two sides still have differences on some key issues, they have indeed shown a common desire to ease the relations, control the further serious fermentation of differences, and maximize the positive aspects of their relations. 

What’s important is this meeting created a positive atmosphere, which is of special significance as mutual suspicion in 🇨🇳-🇺🇸 relations deepens and the atmosphere of people-to-people friendship weakens. The two heads of state had an intimate conversation and took a walk together. After the meeting, President Biden walked President Xi to the car door. These provide an implicit additional reference for the world to interpret the nature of 🇨🇳-🇺🇸 relations. 

What’s most worrying is that 🇺🇸 political environment is complicated and there are uncontrollable destructive factors in 🇨🇳-🇺🇸 relations. Hopefully that time will prove that America as a whole is rational.

Chinese society currently has three major issues with the US:

1. On the Taiwan question, 🇺🇸 condones the DPP authorities’ “Taiwan independence” tendency.
2. 🇺🇸 has intensified its efforts to suppress Chinese high-tech enterprises, tightening the curbs on China’s semiconductor technology, and engaging in “decoupling & disconnection” to contain China.
3. 🇺🇸 publicly incites the Philippines and others to provoke China in the South China Sea. It has repeatedly acted presumptuously, threatening the security of China’s islands and reefs.

If 🇺🇸 doesn’t make any adjustments in these three directions and continues to increase its provocative actions, it’ll be hard for the Chinese public to believe that 🇺🇸 is sincere in managing risks in China-US relations.
